<br>
Caster balancing will force them to re-adjust everything anyways.  Since the intent is to make casters more powerful in some way, Verant will have to tweak the difficulty of the mobs regardless unless the caster changes are so minute that it wont make a difference.  What percentage based abilities do is keeps Verant from having to re-adjust everything in the future.  For example, we know PoP will bring many new abilities, and tougher mobs.  Hypothetically, lets say our current DS's were tuned to a percentage of luclin mobs.  The DPS of a damage shield remains pretty consistent in that scenario, and would never really become 'outdated' in the manner our current damage shield has.  This thread already shows our DS isnt what it once was depending on how high end of a game your playing.  <br>
<br>
Even Quillistar's point in how it really isnt so 'unbalancing' compared to the damage output of some tanks reinforces that it should be percentage based.  Currently, its an outdated spell that becomes less effective the higher you lvl, and i'm not exactly sure that it was intended to be taht way.  Then again, the amount of hp's some mobs have, or their damage output probably werent in the original vision either.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaaeamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaeamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 12:20:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=22>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Personally, i still dont see how CH broke the game.&quot;<br>
<br>
That is because CH did not break the game (e.g. the game works and CH is in it).  However, if you take away CH, most boss mob encounters become impossible as is, or atleast you have to replace each previously CHing Cleric with 5 Clerics (DL), 6 Druids(NT) or 11 Shamen (CB).  The game is not, therefor, broken by CH, but the entire game IS built on CH.  IMO, it would be a better game without it (alternatively, it would be a margiially better game if CH simply were not monopolized by one class).<br>
<br>
&quot;I think its a crucial ability that makes sense for Clerics, and only Clerics to have.&quot;<br>
<br>
That is arbitratry.  You will be incapable of supporting that arguement without resorting to one of two things: 1. That is the way the game has been, 2. Some mushy RP style rationale (e.g &quot;The Vision&quot;).  CH is an ability in the game.  There is no rational reason it has to be the exclusive domain of Clerics, it simply is.<br>
<br>
&quot;It has a major aggro factor, and encounters arent trivial because of CH, with the way mobs are attuned to its aggro and some boss mobs damage output.&quot;<br>
<br>
No.  It doesn't.  Quite the opposite is true, I suspect.  There are fights in the game where CHs are required to land (not be cast) within the first 1-2 seconds of a fight (AoW).  The result is not agro immediately shifting to the Cleric.  I suspect, if only to make such fights possible, that CH has a drastically reduced agro effect, at least as to certain mobs, compared to healing the same amount by other spells.<br>
<br>
&quot;With or without CH, the mobs would be tuned to similar states of difficulty in some other manner.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yeah, I would hope so.  That is kind of the point.  It would be nice if the game were balanced, fun, and very challanging, without reliance on a single spell avilable only to a single class. <p>____________<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13463"
