Veeshan Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubroomhilda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broomhilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 1:10:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> &quot;There is no rational reason it has to be the exclusive domain of Clerics, it simply is.&quot;<br>
<br>
See, i disagree here.  I know people have stated Clerics can solo, and do this and that, but honestly, clerics cant do nearly as much as other classes because their focus is healing, and thats basically their sole responsibility in groups.  They have one all-powerful group ability that makes them needed-wanted, people arent picking clerics up for much else than their ability to heal.  The fact taht they have CH makes them the unquestioned healers of the game.  I see no reason why a druid or shaman should get CH at all.  Even the whole 'fantasy' idea of a cleric has to do with healing, what sense would it make if druids or shamans were just as good or even almost?  Clerics cant whine because they have the most powerful ability in the game even if they think its boring, or forces them to rely on one thing.  Druids and Shamans cant whine about CH, because Clerics are very limited in their other abilities.  It somewhat balances out in the end, better than many other scenario's.<br>
<br>
From what i understand then, the issue seems to be people are just sick of the CH routine.  Which doesnt mean CH is broke, as Aemdaar stated.  But to be honest being sick of something isnt a valid reason to change something that would take almost a total overhaul to change.  Imo, the CH-MT routine works even though its the principal idea behind every encounter, and people might be sick of death of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushadowsend.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowsend</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 1:12:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> As a player that 2-boxes a paladin and druid quite, often I've seen the diminishing returns of a damage shield with each expansion. In fact the continued decline in effectiveness of damage shields prompted me to complete the 8th Coldain ring quest, extra 8 pts add up.<br>
<br>
One option is a damage shield that is a percentage, 10% as an example, of the recipients total HPs. This would typically give a damage shield between 50 to 70 HPs on a raid-buffed tank. It would also scale, to a degree, with the level of the recipient.<br>
<br>
Alternatively, a stackable damage shield would be interesting. Allow multiple druids to cast a specific stacking spell until a damage limit is reached. The base damage of the spell would have to slightly lower then expected but allow for more then four or five casts to stack.<br>
<br>
Just a few thoughts for the day. <br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50602">Shadowsend Pen`Dragoon</a> <br>
Deepwater Crusader on 
Tarew Marr<br>
Friend to some.<br>
Loved by one.<br>
Devoted to her.<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 1:14:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <b>Ironic that CH, which admittedly broke the game and it is a proportial heal is being used as proof that a percentage DS is a good idea.</b><br>
<br>
Not a "good idea."  A necessary change if DS are to have relevance in a game in which Slow and CH exist.<br>
<br>
And it's not so much that CH has broken the game, it's that the game has evolved past the point where CH wasn't disproportionate.  Think way, way back before any expansions when we all maxxed at 50.   <br>
<br>
So, the real question is how to make DS relevant in a world where mobs have close to a million HPs and hit for 500-1000 per hit.   And how not to have that DS adversely affect the lower and mid level games.<br>
<br>
Proportional DS is the answer.  At lower levels, a good spike job can do more damage to the mob than the damage it does, so a proportional DS would be much worse than any of the existing spikes.   A proportional DS really becomes effective only against the higher level mobs that hit for 140+ damage per hit.   Make it a single target DS with the same duration as our top blades, but at twice the mana cost.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A> at: 5/28/02 11:27:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaaeamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaeamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 2:22:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> &quot;It somewhat balances out in the end, better than many other scenario's.&quot;<br>
