<br>
Point taken, if you're looking at damage mitigation in its most literal meaning. However, there is more than one type of damage mitigation in this game, and if there wasn't, there would be no advantage at all in bringing most classes onto raids.<br>
<br>
In that broader sense of the word, Enchanters mitigate damage by removing a mob from play until the party is ready to focus its attention on that mob. Wizards mitigate damage with nukes; the more quickly a mob is defeated, the less overall damage it does to your party. <br>
<br>
Case in point: any significant amount of damage, regardless of its source (nuke, DoT, DS), is a mitigating factor in the amount of damage a mob can do to your party. <br>
<br>
