  If they had never given CH to Clerics, they would've gotten something to compensate.  Yes, they are the top tier among healers, and they deserve some distinction; but not SO much that it makes a raid force sit on their @#%$ waiting on more clerics to log on.  If people would prefer the game to continue this way, that is their deal.  I on the other hand, would like to see some actual skill involved where REAL strategy must be used to bring down a MoB; not just changing the CH cycle by a couple seconds to compensate for how hard a MoB hits.   <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171494</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urumand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rumand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 6:06:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DS or Slow: Which is better?</span><hr size=1> Hmmmm.... an interesting idea. How about a damage shield that is based on how HARD a mob hits you.<br>
