 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usorrun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorrun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 6:09:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Aidon, sure there is to make it fair... the only balance to DS power now is that its overall effectiveness decreases as we level (and that it steals the kill if nobody hits the mob).  If that is changed then there has to be some balance to that.<br>
<br>
I suspect the only reason dmg shields dont make resist checks now is the possiblity for those checks to put unreasonable load on the servers.  It has nothing to do with class balance.  At any given time there are many druids and mages casting dmg shields on the tanks across a server and if there was a resist check for each hit, that could potentially bog down a CPU but would definately add alot of overhead to the proccessor.  If the mob got only one resist on the first hit then it would defeat the purpose... players would just cancel the DS and recast until one stuck.  Tedious, but not really that much of a power balance.<br>
