Unresistable 10% DS.  Mob hits for 600, it takes 60 points of damage every time it hits.  Mob hits for 1100? It takes 110. Mob hits the tank for 50, it takes 5.  Plenty of balance there, imo.  Make it stack with Bard bracer, ranger ac/ds buffs, hell make it stack with mage DS so they don't bitch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/02 8:14:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Scirocco says:  <b><i>A damage shield that reflected a substantial percentage of the damage inflicted (20-25%, perhaps), or a percentage of the mob's hitpoints, would make a DS actually useful in the top-end game.</b></i><br>
<br>
Before you automatically jump the "top-end game", where balancing damage shields would be <i>most</i> difficult, think about how they would do it for just the 50+ XP game.<br>
<br>
Proportional damage is a good suggestion but I see two problems:  (1) I don't think the game coding can handle such spell mechanics and (2) even if it could, to what would you set the percentage?  If it's to be based on pre-Kunark, it should be around 40-50%, which could cause severe game imbalances.  Or should pre-Kunark be nerfed as part of this percentage process?<br>
<br>
In raids, the problems only get worse.  Given the massive amount of melee damage of some of these NPCs, one druid casting one simple spell could end up doing the offensive damage of several other classes combined.  At the same time, a single damage shield spell wouldn't make druids more desirable because (a) mages have would it too and (b) only one member of the class would be required to make it work.<br>
<br>
I think an easy-to-code solution which would help out the higher level game would be a 50% upgrade to the level 58 spell, to give it a value of 48 per hit.  Also, the anti-twink solution should be improved to prevent this spell being cast on anyone below, say, level 52. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/29/02 12:49:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27426.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.engtong.com/Valoran/images/60x60/aidon60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I think an easy-to-code solution which would help out the higher level game would be a 50% upgrade to the level 58 spell, to give it a value of 48 per hit.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
